New Records: Austria won the group and will play the runners-up from Group F (one of Turkey, Czech Republic and Georgia) in the last 16
Key Match Events: Marcel Sabitzer scored the winning goal for Austria in the 80th minute
Memphis Depay scored a goal for the Netherlands to make it 2-2
Wout Weghorst continued the theme of this being a summer for the return of big strikers with involvement in Memphis Depay's goal
Pre-Game Insights: Austria were considered dark horses for Euro 2024 before this game
Rangnick said before the tournament started, should Austria squeeze through they will fancy their chances of beating anybody
Post-Match Reflections: Ronald Koeman said: 'It was very bad. We did not control the match early; later on, we performed slightly better and we had a few opportunities, but they punished us'
Rangnick said: 'It's incredible to finish top of the group that was the hardest possible on based on UEFA coefficients'
Miscellaneous Highlights: Marcel Sabitzer is Austria's talisman and was impressive in his central floating role
Memphis Depay is now just four goals off the all-time scoring record for his country with 46 goals
